<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Keys in yaml files containing dashes are broken and end up with only the last part of the key:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
router:
  routes:
    my-route:
      route: my/route
</code></pre>

<p>...will result in...</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
router:
  routes:
    route:
      route: my/route
</code></pre>

<p>This is due the regex using /w, and is easily fixed by adding the dash (line 134).</p>

<p>I know, the documentation states 'specifying other parsers should you want more complex syntax' but just for a dash this seems overkill, especially as the other config classes DO support them.</p>

    </div>
